		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			The main thing I am looking for is a reasonably long duration haste spell that is the same speed as Celerity.<br><br>Ever since the haste potions I will admit having been slightly miffed that even at 150% percent extension the best we can manage is about 24 minutes and the potions are 30 minutes.  A group haste might be nice since the only times we haste are in groups without an Enchanter or Shaman and soloing.  It would be a burden to those who solo and not in line with our other buffs so I think our best chance would be to ask for a single version.<br><br>My personal opinion would be to ask for a haste spell that is a 30 minute base duration, 50 percent and single shot, runs 370 to 400 mana, and is a level 66 to 68 spell.<br><br>This setup is a little less than double the duration Celerity and about twice the mana.  The Devs have shown I think with the recent SA change they are willing to double spell duration for double the mana.  I would prefer the spell be at 66 to fill out that spell level but it might be strange for Beastlords that just got Celerity at 65.  It does require a rune though and there are alot of other things in the game that dont make total sense. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br><br>Kat<p>Message Edited by Katonis on <span class=date_text>11-04-2005</span> <span class=time_text>11:43 AM</span>
