			<DIV>I don't think there should be a much of a question about increasing the duration, but seeing what they did to SA I could guarantee if the same type of thing happened with celerity most Bsts probably just would not bother with it and use the potions.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Currently it is 185 mana with a duration of 12.7 mins @L39 to 16.0 mins @L50 (Note: It is a level 39 enchanter spell). So keeping in mind that the lower level enchanters also use this spell until they get <SPAN class=rr>Swift like the Wind at level 47 (250 mana with a duration of 15.1 mins @L47 to 16.0 mins @L50 [60% haste]) adding more than 65 to the mana cost would be skewing it very badly for the chanters since most level 39 chanters already feel the mana pool bite to keep haste on 3 people in a grp with the size of a mana pool available at that level 39, although the duration extension would be an assest to them at that point too.</SPAN></DIV>	
