			>
			If I had to make a choice between the two, I'd prefer a group version of Celerity over a longer duration version of the single target version, but either would be an improvement.<br><br>The most annoying things about our haste right now is cast times.  Sometimes we end up being in a group with 4 other melee's and no haster.  Casting that 5 times every 20 minutes at nearly 10 seconds per cast is pretty annoying.  A group version would help this.  The other thing is with the addition of Bestial Empathy our 9-gem spell bar just became more crowded because we like it so much.  So, when I'm out soloing my template is usually 1-Ancient Nuke 2-Slow 3-Bestial Empathy 4-Growl of the Panther 5-Pet Heal 6-Single Target Heal, 7-Pet Haste, 8-Pet Proc and 9-Regen.  I guess I'm just old fashioned keeping pet haste and pet proc memmed at all times, a habit learned from my early years when pet haste didnt last very long, but it also comes in handy on those rare occasions where something happens to the pet while you are being beat on.  I can re-cast, pet haste and proc without sitting to try and re-mem spells.  In any case, with a template like that there is no room for Celerity.  If it was a longer duration, it wouldnt be so bad.<br><br>Off topic Tastain but me and a couple of other beastlords were talking about this in regards to our dps.  We'd like to see Bestial Empathy changed from a 1.5 second cast time to .5 sec like our ice nukes were changed.  It would improve our dps even more by eliminating the lost melee time when casting.  See if you can get that changed for us =)
