		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I wanted empathy lowered in casting time since it hit beta.  However, it is more of a dot than a nuke and most of our nukes have a 3.0(base) casting time, so the 1.5 seems to fit.  I will bring it up again, but not sure we'll see that aspect of the spell changed.<br><br>As far as haste I think the major issues for most beastlords are mana cost, duration, casting time.  Some do want a group version, but what worries me about that is the mana cost issue.  If you are solo'n, if you are in a group with 4 casters, if one person happens to die, etc then you wind up in a situation where you are spending lots of mana for very little return.  Also making a group version would completely change the spell, we'd likely either have to get a brand new spell (another rune turn in or something) or we'd have to aquire it some different way.  By simply making some tweaks to celerity then it's possible to keep the spell the same, adjust SLTW and maybe WR and leave most other haste spells as is.<br><br>By lowering the casting time on haste and bumping the duration some then it still becomes easier to maintain on a group and time spent casting the buff goes down.  At the sametime beastlords that solo or find themselves in groups where 3+ people click off haste won't have as many problems either.<br><br>If the base duration went up, the casting time went down a bit, and there was a "reasonable" boost to mana cost would that come closest to making most people happy?  I know it's impossible for everyone to be happy lol, but atm this seems like the one that gives the most people mostly what they want with the least issues for those that might not quite want it this way.  *shrugs*	
		</td></tr>
