		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			"I've even started carring speed potions around simply because its the same haste / duration as Celerity and i dont have to worry about memming a spell for it nor the cast times."<br><br>Duration is actually much higher on potions than spell.  Spell maxes at 16min base right now, Even with 50% extention it's still only ~24 min duration; whereas the potions are 30mins.<br><br>One suggestion that has come up recently and seems pretty reasonable is simply adjusting the scaling of the spell level/duration.  Right now celerity goes from 12.7mins at 39 to 16mins at 50.  If a small tweak were made to the base duration/interval,then the spell could have ~30min base duration at 70 without really changing the lower end progression from 39 to 50.  This seems to be a nice solution as it makes the spell more reasonable for those that get it later(bst/63, shm/56), but doesn't really change it much in terms of power/mana at the lower end.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
