<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=beastlordbalance&message.id=3309#M3309">14</a> of 25
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 539 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Like with most spells and issues in a game the size of EQ you have to look at what's around you.&nbsp; I'd like to see the casting time dropped on celerity as well, but looking at other haste spells that seems very unlikely unless they did a major overhaul.&nbsp; One of the things I've tried to do is keep change requests as focused as possible because they are easier to see/do without major reprocussions or requiring a lot of balancing before being implemented.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>SLTW also has an 8sec casting time, although a's quickening is only 4 atm, but WR is back up to 7.&nbsp; The augment line of haste for enc runs differently than the pure hastes, but VoG and SoV are both at 6seconds.&nbsp; There does seem to be some room for adjusting the casting time as well, but I'm unsure what would be done there and it would hit multiple other spells.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The other thing to keep in mind though is that even though it would still be taking 8seconds(base) to cast the spell, baring a death or something you just wouldn't have to recast it nearly as often, so your total time casting would go down some even if the actual casting time wasn't changed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As I said this is still very much in the discussion phase and wanting to make sure lots of beastlords can see where others are at and why before we really push for one change over another.&nbsp; Please keep the discussion going and civil.&nbsp; 8)</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>11-11-2005</span> <span class=time_text>11:19 AM</span>
		</span>
