		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			45 to 55 minute durtiaon single target haste would be fine so long as they kept the mana cost reasonable.  Half the people you group haste will click it off and group spells generally cost 3 to 4 times more mana just because it is a group spell.  If you keep it single target and a reasonable mana cost it would be much more efficient most of the time.<br><br>Group IoS was removed at the request of the beastlord community as it didn't fit where they put it in.  The old spell only dropped in area where it was of no use to the beastlords who got it.  Yes they should probubly add it again at a lower level and more available means.   <br><br>Group focus would be nice for those times when there isn't a shaman around willing to wunshi your group.<br><br>Growl is fine how it is.  It was designed to help beastlord dps not seperate the gap in dps further.  If growl was a group spell rogue, monk, berserker, and ranger dps would jump a lot while ours would stay where it currently is.  The spell was designed to help our dps not our utility.<br><br>Something needs to be done about ferocity of irionu but again you are suggesting it be made way more powerful than intended.  keeping its current form while possibly doubling duration and changing the stamina portion for more to the resist portion is one idea that i personally like.  Alternatively giving it Crit chance, a proc, a double attack chance, etc would also be acceptable changes.<br><br>Why is combining these very unrelated buffs a good idea?  Raiding beastlords rarely use any of them and in groups the only one of any real need is shrew.  <br><br>If you aren't allowed to bring a pet on raids I suggest you talk to your raid leader outside of raid times and explain that in doing that they eliminate a good portion of your dps and that you can controll the pet.  Ask to try this out on a few mobs that are trivial for your current raids to show what you mean.  Then slowly ask if you can bring it on more challenging encounters.  There aer a few encounter that some people deam no pet but if you take a sensable and calm path you can break a raid leader of the no pet at all habbit.	
